# Engine Purity

- Do not use browser globals in engine code (`window`, `document`, `fetch`, `localStorage`, `indexedDB`, `performance`, `requestAnimationFrame`).
- Do not import from `react`, `pixi.js`, `@pixi/*`, `src/ui/**`, or `src/render/**`.
- Talk to external systems only through ports/interfaces.
- Treat engine world as single source of truth.
- Place write intents in `src/engine/commands/` as discriminated unions.
- Keep system files named `*System.ts`.
- When adding a new system, also add a debug hook/snapshot path for UI debug toggles.
